        "l": {
          "type": "faq_list",
          "settings": {
            "q1_question": "How long does shipping take?",
            "q1_answer": "Orders are processed within 1–3 business days. Standard delivery is 8–14 days because we ship directly from our overseas contract manufacturer to keep prices fair. We'll send tracking the moment it dispatches — and you can reply to any order email if you need an ETA.",
            "q2_question": "What's your return policy?",
            "q2_answer": "30-day money-back guarantee, no questions asked. If you're not happy with your results, email us and we'll refund you in full — even if the box is opened.",
            "q3_question": "Is this safe to use during pregnancy?",
            "q3_answer": "Yes. Our formula uses goat milk, niacinamide, glycerin, and allantoin — all pregnancy-safe. Unlike most foot peels, we contain no salicylic acid, no glycolic acid, and no essential oils. If you have any concerns, check with your OB-GYN first.",
            "q4_question": "Can I use this if I'm diabetic?",
            "q4_answer": "Yes — the formula is gentle and free of harsh acids that diabetics are typically warned to avoid. As always, consult your doctor if you have severe peripheral neuropathy or open wounds.",
            "q5_question": "How is this different from Baby Foot?",
            "q5_answer": "Baby Foot uses a strong acid blend (glycolic, lactic, salicylic) that causes dramatic peeling 3–7 days after application. We use a goat milk + niacinamide hydrating formula that softens skin gradually without the painful peel. Better for sensitive skin, pregnancy, diabetes, and anyone who can't be barefoot in public for a week.",
            "q6_question": "How fast will I see results?",
            "q6_answer": "Most customers see softer, more hydrated feet after one 30-minute session. For deeply cracked heels, we recommend 2–3 applications spaced a week apart for best results.",
            "q7_question": "Can I use it on my hands and elbows too?",
            "q7_answer": "Absolutely. The same formula works on dry hands, rough elbows, and even knees. Many customers buy the 3-pack specifically to use across multiple body areas.",
            "q8_question": "How often should I use it?",
            "q8_answer": "Once every 2–4 weeks for maintenance, or weekly during dry seasons (winter, sandal season, heavy beach trips). It's safe to use as often as needed."
          }
        }
